						<summary>

						

						<p>On a slab set up near the same place.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1479, Piṅgaḷa, Śrāvaṇa ba. 5, Thursday = 1557 A.D., August 14; f.d.t. ·02. The week-day was Saturday.</hi></p>						

						<p>It refers to the obeisance of the people, probably to the deity (details lost) and to an image of single stone.</p>						

